#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:13
msgid ""
"In previous lessons, you learned how to create arrays to store lists of "
"values and how to loop over them. That's useful, but arrays can do much more."
msgstr ""
"在之前的课程中，你学习了如何创建数组来存储多个值，以及如何遍历数组。这很有用"
"，但数组的功能远不止于此。"

msgid ""
"The real strength of GDScript arrays is that you can add and remove values "
"from them at any time. This lets you build waiting lines of data or piles of "
"data. We call these [i]queues[/i] and [i]stacks[/i], respectively. We'll see "
"what that means in this lesson."
msgstr ""
"GDScript数组的真正强大之处在于，你可以随时向其中添加或从中移除值。这使你能够"
"构建数据队列或数据堆。我们分别称之为[i]队列[/i]（queue）和[i]堆栈[/i]（stack"
"）。在本课中，我们将了解这些术语的含义。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:25
msgid "Let's look at a concrete example."
msgstr "让我们来看一个具体的例子。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:33
msgid "Tracking orders in a restaurant management game"
msgstr "在餐厅管理游戏中追踪订单"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:35
msgid ""
"You're making a restaurant management game where customers place orders, and "
"you need to handle them one by one."
msgstr "假设你在做一个餐厅管理游戏，顾客们会下单，而你需要逐一处理这些订单。"

msgid ""
"In the example below, customers order meals that end up in a waiting line (a "
"queue). You need to prepare them in the kitchen. We simulate orders arriving "
"and getting completed over time."
msgstr ""
"在下面的例子中，顾客点餐后，订单会排成一条等候队列。你需要在厨房里备餐。我们"
"模拟的是订单不断到来、然后逐一完成的过程。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:57
msgid "How do you keep track of pending and completed orders? With an array!"
msgstr "如何追踪待处理和已完成的订单？使用数组！"

msgid ""
"When a customer purchases a meal, you want to [i]append[/i] (add) it to the "
"array. Then, as you complete a meal in the kitchen and serve it, you want to "
"remove it from the array."
msgstr ""
"顾客购买餐点时，你需要将它[i]append[/i]（追加）到数组中。然后，当你在厨房完成"
"一道菜并端上桌时，就需要把它从数组中移除。"

msgid ""
"You can use the [code]append()[/code] function to add values at the end of "
"an array. To remove values from the start, you can use the [code]pop_front()"
"[/code] function. We call it \"pop\" because the value jumps out of the "
"array."
msgstr ""
"你可以用 [code]append()[/code] 函数在数组末尾添加值。要从数组开头移除值，可以"
"用 [code]pop_front()[/code] 函数。之所以叫 \"pop\"，是因为值会从数组中弹出来"
"。"

msgid ""
"Try to read the code below before moving on. Don't worry if not everything "
"makes sense, as we'll break it all down."
msgstr ""
"在继续之前，先试着读一下下面的代码。如果一时不能完全理解也别担心，我们会逐一"
"拆解。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:83
msgid ""
"Notice how we call some functions by writing a dot after a variable name. "
"Just like some values have variables you can access with a dot (like the "
"[code]x[/code] variable in [code]position.x[/code]), they can also have "
"their own functions."
msgstr ""
"注意，有些函数是通过在变量名后面加点号（.）来调用的。就像某些值带有可以通过点"
"号访问的子变量（比如 [code]position.x[/code] 中的 [code]x[/code]），它们也可"
"以拥有自己的函数。"

msgid ""
"Functions like [code]append()[/code] and [code]pop_front()[/code] only exist "
"on arrays. To call them, we need to write the array name, then a dot, then "
"the function: [code]array_name.append()[/code]."
msgstr ""
"像 [code]append()[/code] 和 [code]pop_front()[/code] 这样的函数只属于数组。要"
"调用它们，需要先写数组名，然后加一个点号，再写函数名：[code]array_name.append"
"()[/code]。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:95
msgid ""
"Let's break down the code. We add orders to the [code]waiting_orders[/code] "
"array by appending them."
msgstr ""
"我们来拆解一下代码。我们通过追加的方式，把订单添加到 [code]waiting_orders[/"
"code] 数组中。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:115
msgid ""
"We can use a string to represent a meal when calling the [code]add_order()[/"
"code] function."
msgstr "在调用 [code]add_order()[/code] 函数时，我们可以用字符串来表示一道菜品。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:135
msgid ""
"When completing an order, we remove it from the [code]waiting_orders[/code] "
"array by calling its [code]pop_front()[/code] function. This function gives "
"us the order back, which allows us to assign it to a temporary variable."
msgstr ""
"完成一份订单时，我们调用 [code]waiting_orders[/code] 数组的 [code]pop_front()"
"[/code] 函数，将订单从数组中移除。这个函数会把那份订单返回给我们，这样我们就"
"可以把它赋给一个临时变量。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:155
msgid ""
"We can then append the order to our [code]completed_orders[/code] array."
msgstr "然后我们就可以把这份订单追加到 [code]completed_orders[/code] 数组中。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:175
msgid ""
"When we use an array this way, we call it a [i]queue[/i]: the first element "
"we add to the array is the first one we remove. It's like a waiting line at "
"a store."
msgstr ""
"以这种方式使用数组时，我们称之为[i]队列[/i]（queue）：最先加入数组的元素会最"
"先被移除。就像商店里的排队队伍一样。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:183
msgid "What does #... mean?"
msgstr "#... 是什么意思？"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:185
msgid ""
"We write [code]#...[/code] to show that there is more code here. The three "
"dots mean \"we are not showing all the code.\" We use this to break down "
"code examples and make them easier to learn from."
msgstr ""
"我们写 [code]#...[/code] 来表示此处还有更多代码。三个点号的意思是「我们没有展"
"示全部代码」。我们用它来拆解代码示例，让代码更容易学习。"

msgid ""
"The hash sign ([code]#[/code]) marks the start of a code comment. It's a "
"line the computer will ignore, which is why it typically appears in grey."
msgstr ""
"井号（[code]#[/code]）标志着一行代码注释的开始。井号后面的一整行内容都会被计"
"算机忽略，这也是为什么注释通常显示为灰色。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:195
msgid "Using arrays as stacks"
msgstr "把数组用作堆栈"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:197
msgid "Another common use of arrays is [i]stacks[/i] of data."
msgstr "数组的另一个常见用途是数据的[i]堆栈[/i]（stack）。"

msgid ""
"Take a factory management game where you need to retrieve materials from "
"stacks of crates. They arrive at the factory piled up vertically, and you "
"need to take them from top to bottom."
msgstr ""
"以一个工厂管理游戏为例，你需要从一摞摞箱子中取出材料。箱子到达工厂时会垂直堆"
"叠起来，你需要从上往下取用。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:219
msgid ""
"To take a crate from the back of the array, this time, we use the "
"[code]pop_back()[/code] array function."
msgstr "这次，要从数组尾部取出一个箱子，我们用 [code]pop_back()[/code] 这个数组函数。"

msgid ""
"This function removes (pops) the last value from the array and returns it to "
"you."
msgstr "这个函数会从数组中移除（弹出）最后一个值，并把它返回给你。"

msgid ""
"Here we pop the last value of the array and print what's left of the array "
"to demonstrate how the array gets smaller."
msgstr ""
"这里我们弹出数组的最后一个值，然后打印数组中剩余的部分，演示数组是如何逐渐变"
"小的。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:243
msgid ""
"Like [code]pop_front()[/code], the function returns the value removed from "
"the array. You will often store that value in a variable. This value could "
"be the crate's content, which you can then use to give resources to the "
"player."
msgstr ""
"和 [code]pop_front()[/code] 一样，该函数会返回从数组中移除的那个值。你通常会"
"把这个值存到一个变量中。这个值可以是箱子里的内容物，然后你就可以用它来为玩家"
"提供资源。"

msgid ""
"When we use an array this way, we call it a [i]stack[/i]: the last element "
"we add is the first one we remove. It's like a pile of plates where you take "
"from the top."
msgstr ""
"以这种方式使用数组时，我们称之为[i]堆栈[/i]（stack）：最后加入的元素会最先被"
"移除。就像一摞盘子，你总是从最上面开始拿。"

msgid ""
"In the following practices, you will use the [code]append()[/code], "
"[code]pop_front()[/code], and [code]pop_back()[/code] array functions."
msgstr ""
"在接下来的练习中，你会用到 [code]append()[/code]、[code]pop_front()[/code] "
"和 [code]pop_back()[/code] 这三个数组函数。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:255
msgid "Completing orders"
msgstr "完成订单"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:256
msgid "The [code]waiting_orders[/code] array will be filled over time."
msgstr "[code]waiting_orders[/code] 数组会随着时间的推移逐渐被填满。"

msgid ""
"Your job is to move orders from the waiting list to the "
"[code]completed_orders[/code] list using the array's [code]append()[/code] "
"and [code]pop_front()[/code] functions."
msgstr ""
"你的任务是使用数组的 [code]append()[/code] 和 [code]pop_front()[/code] 函数，"
"把订单从等候列表转移到 [code]completed_orders[/code] 列表中。"

msgid ""
"Remember that the array's [code]pop_front()[/code] function returns the "
"popped value, which allows you to store it in a variable and then pass it to "
"another function."
msgstr ""
"请记住，数组的 [code]pop_front()[/code] 函数会返回被弹出的值，这意味着你可以"
"把它存到变量里，再传递给其他函数。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:274
msgid ""
"Orders are piling up in the kitchen, and we need to clear them fast using "
"the array's [code]pop_front()[/code] function."
msgstr ""
"厨房里的订单越堆越多，我们需要用数组的 [code]pop_front()[/code] 函数尽快处理"
"掉它们。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:279
msgid "Clearing up the crates"
msgstr "清理箱子"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:280
msgid ""
"Crates are piling up on the platform. Move them out of the way by popping "
"them from the [code]crates[/code] array."
msgstr "箱子在平台上越堆越多。从 [code]crates[/code] 数组中把它们弹出来，腾出空间。"

msgid ""
"You need to remove them from top to bottom using the array's [code]pop_back()"
"[/code] function."
msgstr "你需要用数组的 [code]pop_back()[/code] 函数，从上到下依次移除它们。"

msgid "Your code should remove all the crates in the array using a while loop."
msgstr "你的代码应该用 while 循环来移除数组中所有的箱子。"

msgid ""
"[b]Careful![/b] If you write the while loop incorrectly, you can freeze the "
"program."
msgstr "[b]小心！[/b]如果 while 循环写错了，可能会导致程序卡死。"

msgid ""
"You can check if the [code]crates[/code] array still has values by writing "
"[code]while crates:[/code]. This works because an empty array counts as "
"[code]false[/code], and an array with items counts as [code]true[/code]."
msgstr ""
"你可以通过写 [code]while crates:[/code] 来检查 [code]crates[/code] 数组是否还"
"有值。之所以可以这样做，是因为空数组被视为 [code]false[/code]，而有内容的数组"
"被视为 [code]true[/code]。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:301
msgid ""
"Crates are piling up on the platform. Move them out of the way by popping "
"them from their array."
msgstr "箱子在平台上越堆越多。从数组中把它们弹出来，腾出空间。"

#: course/lesson-23-append-to-arrays/lesson.tres:305
msgid "Appending and popping values from arrays"
msgstr "从数组中追加和弹出值"

